com.google.enterprise.sdk.onebox
Interface IOneBoxResults

All Known Implementing Classes:
OneBoxResults
public interface IOneBoxResults

Interface that must be implemented by classes encapsulating OneBox for Enterprise result sets. This interface is used in the OneBoxProvider.processRequest() method to write out an HTTP response to the OneBox request.

Your OneBoxProvider can create a custom results set object as long as it implements this interface.

See Also:
OneBoxProvider, OneBoxResults

Method Summary
 java.lang.String serialize()
          Returns an XML String that describes a OneBox results set and adheres to Google's OneBox for Enterprise response Schema.
